    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An American Town Meeting: The Issue Is Race; The Cubans</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ray Fisher letter, responding to June 5 article Best of Friends, Worlds Apart, in series How Race Is Lived in America, questions whether Americans who have called for Elian Gonzalez to remain in US would have felt the same if he were black</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Best of Friends, Worlds Apart'' (front page, June 5):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Best of Friends, Worlds Apart'' (front page, June 5):</p>
        <p>As a resident of Miami for more than 60 years, I have wondered since the start of the Elian Gonzalez drama if the Americans who have favored his remaining in the United States would have reacted the same way had Elian been black.</p>
        <p>RAY FISHER  New York, June 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
